	<span class="csC2FEE544">Introduced</span></p><p class="cs3E63B65"><span class="cs8498B7A6">House Bill 5239</span></p><p class="csFF933113"><span class="csADC6E5DB">By Delegates Hornbuckle, Lewis, and Hansen</span></p><p class="cs8BEF69CE"><span class="cs7B75DFFE">[Introduced February 05, 2026; referred to the Committee on Education then Finance]</span></p><p class="cs29F66C3F"><span class="csEF05ACC">A BILL to amend and reenact &sect;18A-4-2 of the Code of West Virginia, 1931, as amended, relating to </span><a name="_Hlk189237746"><span class="csEF05ACC">raising the state minimum salary schedule for teachers; and raising the state minimum salary for teachers to $50,000.</span></a></p><p class="cs63FD752D"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Be it enacted by the Legislature of West Virginia:</span></p><p class="cs63FD752D"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">&nbsp;</span></p><h2 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="cs7A33E2F1">ARTICLE 4. SALARIES, WAGES AND OTHER BENEFITS.</span></h2>
	<h4 class="cs7F45F1B">
